article.headline: Harvard 65, Vermont 57
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Brian Cusworth scored 17 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and Jim Goffredo added 15 points Saturday in leading Harvard to an 65-57 win over Vermont. Harvard (1-0), which led by two at halftime, opened a 50-39 lead midway through the second half, but then went more than 7 minutes without scoring. Four turnovers in that period helped the Catamounts tie the game at 50-50. Zach Martin then sank a 3-pointer from the corner to give Harvard a 53-50 edge, but the Catamounts fought back, leading by one point with 2:03 left. But a 3-pointer by Goffredo and reverse layup by Cusworth gave Harvard a lead they wouldn't relinquish. Vermont's Ryan Schneider had a career-high 19 points, and led both teams in scoring. Harvard outrebounded Vermont 41-33 and Matt Stehle had a game high 11 rebounds.
